description:
We need a way to adjust cohort metrics. the issue is mainly for planet art but can happen for other clients also
The Appsflyer reports cohort metrics including organic data but planet art provides organic data in Separate S3 files. Specifically new_orders_7d in this case. So, this metric's value gets inflated while aggregating. So, we need an adjustment to that.

We are using below config in data consolidation config for each region
            "OrganicMetricsUpdateConfig" : {
                "OrganicMetricsUpdateEnabled" : true,
                "OrganicMetricsToUpdateList" : [
                    "NewOrders7d"
                ]
            }

We have few clients which requires ingestion of offline data which doesn't have operating_system and AppId specified in the CSV records. We duplicate the record for both Android and IOS and the Market share calculator will split the Cost accordingly.

Example clients : Brigit, Planet Art

Advertiser config needs this field as below. Note that we cannot use network ids here because this is part of data import.

    "AdvertiserConfig" : {
        "LookbackWeeks" : NumberInt(6),
        "WeeklyGrouping" : NumberInt(2),
        "FileDiscoveryConfig" : {
            *****
        },
        "DateRangeConfig" : {
            ******
        },
        "OfflineNetworks" : [
            "Affiliate",
            "Grocery TV Ads",
            "Rokt"
        ]
    }
